   "source": [
    "# Reproduction Logbook: NonZero (ICML 2026, OpenReview Jh6gq9QsFa)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Paper:** \"NonZero: Interaction-Guided Exploration for Multi-Agent Monte\n",
    "Carlo Tree Search\" (arXiv 2605.00751)\n",
    "**Status:** Partial reproduction, published. Claims 1 and 4 (environment +\n",
    "surrogate model) validated at the component level; full end-to-end\n",
    "NonUCT integration not yet complete. Claims 5-6 (SMAC/SMACv2) assessed\n",
    "as infeasible on available compute.\n",
    "**Published submission:** https://huggingface.co/spaces/byte-vortex/nonzero-repro\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Claim-by-claim status\n",
    "\n",
    "### Claim 1 — Low-dimensional nonlinear surrogate + difference operators\n",
    "**Status: Verified (component-level, toy scale).**\n",
    "\n",
    "- Implemented the asinh-GLM surrogate `η(θ,a) = c·asinh(α·⟨θ,a⟩)` exactly\n",
    "  as specified in Section 3.1 (Eq. 2), with joint actions represented as\n",
    "  n-hot vectors in `{0,1}^{n·d}`.\n",
    "- Implemented the first-order difference `Δ_u η` (Eq. 3) and mixed\n",
    "  second-order difference `Δ²_{u,v} η` (Eq. 4).\n",
    "- **Verified the paper's stated identity exactly:**\n",
    "  `η(a^(u,v)) - η(a) = Δ_u η(a) + Δ_v η(a) + Δ²_{u,v} η(a)`,\n",
    "  confirmed to floating-point precision (error ≈ 1.19e-7) via unit test.\n",
    "- Implemented `L_NonUCT` (Eq. 7), the 4-target supervision loss.\n",
    "- **Verified the surrogate can fit real environment reward structure:**\n",
    "  trained on the 8-agent/10-action nonlinear MatGame environment (see\n",
    "  Claim 4 below), converged to R²=0.900 on held-out data — matching the\n",
    "  theoretical ceiling set by the environment's own injected noise\n",
    "  variance (Gaussian σ²=4 + Uniform(-3,3)), meaning the surrogate\n",
    "  recovered essentially all learnable signal.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Not yet done:** the hypernetwork/mixing net (`MixingHyperNet`, per\n",
    "Appendix B.1's `[64,64]` MLP spec) is implemented but not yet wired to\n",
    "real per-agent latent states from a trained MuZero-style representation\n",
    "network — the R²=0.90 result above used a single global θ fit directly\n",
    "to actions, as a simplified test of the model family's expressiveness,\n",
    "not the full state-conditioned architecture.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Claim 2 — Regret bound (Theorem 3.5)\n",
    "**Status: Not attempted.** This is a theoretical claim, checkable by\n",
    "verifying the proof in Appendix A.4 rather than by running code.\n",
    "Deprioritized given time constraints in favor of empirical claims.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Claim 3 — Efficiency separation (Theorem 3.7)\n",
    "**Status: Not attempted.** Same reasoning as Claim 2 — proof\n",
    "verification (Appendix A.6) rather than empirical run.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Claim 4 — MatGame 8-agent/10-action nonlinear benchmark\n",
    "**Status: Partial — infrastructure verified, full NonUCT run pending.**\n",
    "\n",
    "- Built a generalized N-agent, N-action MatGame environment\n",
    "  (`matgame_nonzero.py`) implementing the exact reward rule from\n",
    "  Appendix D: linear setting = sum of agent action indices; nonlinear\n",
    "  setting = linear sum + Gaussian(0, 2²) + Uniform(-3, 3) noise.\n",
    "- Sanity-checked reward scale against Table 1: random-policy episodes\n",
    "  on the 8x10 nonlinear config average ~370-380 (out of a 720 max),\n",
    "  consistent with the paper's trained-baseline range of 587-712 sitting\n",
    "  well above random.\n",
    "- Confirmed the MAZero codebase (which NonZero is built on top of, per\n",
    "  the paper's own Appendix C) builds and trains successfully on Kaggle\n",
    "  T4 GPU — validated end-to-end on the repo's existing `matgame3` config\n",
    "  (converges to optimal joint policy, test score 100.0±0.0 by step 300).\n",
    "- Began implementing NonUCT's selection rule as a C++ patch to MAZero's\n",
    "  MCTS node scoring (`core/mcts/ctree/ctree_sampled/lib/cnode.cpp`):\n",
    "  added a `nonuct_score` field and blended it additively into the\n",
    "  existing pUCT formula, gated by a weight defaulting to 0 so baseline\n",
    "  behavior is unaffected unless explicitly enabled. **This patch compiles\n",
    "  successfully.**\n",
    "- **Not yet done:** the Cython bindings (`cytree.pyx`) needed to call\n",
    "  these new C++ hooks from Python were not implemented, so no NonZero\n",
    "  vs. MAZero training comparison was run. Table 1's actual numbers\n",
    "  (697.1 vs 672.3) were neither reproduced nor falsified.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Claim 5 — SMAC win rate / sample efficiency\n",
    "**Status: Assessed as infeasible on available compute; not attempted.**\n",
    "The official MAZero training recipe (which NonZero extends) targets an\n",
    "NVIDIA A100 80GB per the repository documentation; free-tier Kaggle\n",
    "GPUs (T4/P100, 16GB) are well below this, and SMAC training runs\n",
    "reported in the paper likely require many hours even for baseline\n",
    "methods. A heavily reduced/short-horizon smoke test was considered but\n",
    "would not produce numbers comparable to Table/Figure claims, so was not\n",
    "attempted rather than reporting a misleading partial result.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Claim 6 — SMACv2 win rate + ablations\n",
    "**Status: Assessed as infeasible on available compute; not attempted.**\n",
    "Same reasoning as Claim 5.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Environment / build notes (for anyone reproducing this logbook)\n",
    "\n",
    "- Platform: Kaggle notebook, GPU T4 x1, Python 3.12.\n",
    "- MAZero repo (`github.com/liuqh16/MAZero`) required three build fixes\n",
    "  for this environment:\n",
    "  1. `setup.py`'s `compiler_so.remove('-Wstrict-prototypes')` fails on\n",
    "     compilers where that flag isn't present — patched to a filtered\n",
    "     list comprehension instead of `.remove()`.\n",
    "  2. The repo's pinned Cython 0.29.23 cannot target Python 3.12's\n",
    "     internal C API (`longintrepr.h` relocated) — upgraded to\n",
    "     Cython ≥3.0.10.\n",
    "  3. The repo's pinned `opencv-python==4.5.1.48` has no Python 3.12\n",
    "     wheel and fails building from source — replaced with unpinned\n",
    "     `opencv-python-headless`.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Supporting artifacts\n",
    "\n",
    "- **`nonzero_repro_cleaned.ipynb`** / **`nonzero_full_submission.ipynb`**\n",
    "  — the Kaggle notebook(s) containing the full, runnable pipeline.\n",
    "- **`matgame_nonzero.py`** — the generalized N-agent MatGame environment\n",
    "  (Claim 4).\n",
    "- **`nonzero_surrogate.py`** — the asinh-GLM surrogate + NonUCT\n",
    "  finite-difference operators (Claim 1).\n",
    "- **`validate_surrogate_fit.py`** — the surrogate-fit validation script\n",
    "  (produces the R²=0.90 result cited above).\n",
    "- **`nonuct_cnode_patch.diff`** — the C++ patch adding NonUCT score\n",
    "  hooks to MAZero's MCTS node scoring.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Honesty notes\n",
    "\n",
    "- The exact per-agent reward-index-to-score correspondence in Table 1\n",
    "  is not fully specified in the paper (episode length vs. \"Steps\"\n",
    "  column ambiguity); we inferred `episode_limit=10` by matching the\n",
    "  existing MAZero repo's convention across all its built-in MatGame\n",
    "  variants, and validated this inference against the reported score\n",
    "  magnitudes (see Claim 4 sanity check above) rather than assuming it.\n",
    "- The R²=0.90 surrogate-fit result used a simplified, state-independent\n",
    "  training setup (single global θ) as a first check of model\n",
    "  expressiveness — it is not yet the full architecture the paper\n",
    "  describes, and should not be read as a claim-4-level result on its\n",
    "  own."
